decision decision_semantic_diff_fact_layer {
  name "Semantic diff fact layer — Remogram forge facts, Topogram SDLC semantics"
  description "Post-beta read-only fact inventory extends Remogram with provider-neutral ref and change-request packets for Topogram semantic-diff and branch-workcycle consumers. Remogram owns forge/git/ref/CR facts normalized through schema_version 1 envelopes; Topogram owns lifecycle, queue, proof, and observer routing semantics."
  context ["pitch_semantic_diff_fact_inventory approved on remo", "decision_packet_trust_doctrine accepted", "Six v1 read/plan commands exist without structured ref inventory or CR aggregation", "Topogram observer-snapshot and goal-branch-queue need stable remogram packets without SDLC fields in product output"]
  consequences ["Remogram owns ref inventory facts (ref names, SHAs, default-branch hints, ancestry hints) and change-request fact slices (PR state, checks, mergeability composed from existing pr view/checks/merge plan vocabulary)", "Topogram owns goal_branch lifecycle, task queue selectability, verification/proof semantics, lane routing, and SDLC record mutations — never emitted in remogram JSON", "New fact inventory packet types use forgePacket, SCHEMA_VERSION 1, and FORBIDDEN_PACKET_KEYS; no goal_branch lane sdlc_task queue_selectable or similar keys", "Forge-sourced string leaves follow decision_packet_trust_doctrine; per-field forge_sourced annotation remains optional until a later wave", "Existing six read/plan commands remain authoritative; fact inventory composes and extends them rather than replacing pr view pr checks merge plan or refs compare", "Canonical contract registry lives in packages/remogram-core/contracts/semantic-diff-facts.js; implementation commands land in waves 2–6 per plan_semantic_diff_fact_inventory", "packages/remogram-core and remogram-core skill document the boundary; Remogram packages must not import Topogram runtime"]
  status accepted
}
